</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I would write his name down in my little black book, and wait

<BR>&gt; until until he was a higher level and at least had something to
<BR>&gt; loot. You guys are totally missing my point...your 'punishment'
<BR>&gt; was anything but that..for reasons i have said earlier...your
<BR>&gt; newbie killing only made you feel better, even though it did no
<BR>&gt; harm to the other. If you want to inflict real pain, loot a
<BR>&gt; newly purchased 2h sword, or a hard-earned leather tunic. No
<BR>&gt; that hurts )
<P>If it helps, don't think of this kind of thing as "punishment". Think of it as a "warning". If the guy has half a brain, he'll put two and two together and realize that while he loses nothing (except time)NOW, if he keeps being anti-social, when/if he gets to be higher level he will be KOS back to the stone age.
<P>Personally, I feel that there is NO reasonable justification for spawn-point camping.
